solutions.content:
# Intuition

The idea behind this approach is to use the mathematical property that the sum of the first n odd numbers is n^2, and use this to find the square root of a given integer x.

![1_AF3IpOFN-hyhc08bnQHMSw.webp](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/9cd517e2-8ad9-4d1c-a91f-5a527ab0358f_1674036268.1887174.webp)



# Approach
1. Initialize a variable n to 1, and a variable y to 0.
1. Use a while loop to iterate until y is greater than or equal to x.
1. In each iteration, add 2n-1 to y, and increment n.
1. Once the while loop exits, return n-1 as the square root of x.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:  O(sqrt(n))

- Space complexity: O(1) as the code only uses a few variables and not creating any data structure.
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int mySqrt(int x) {
        // Initializing variables 
        long long y=0,i=3,cnt=0;

        //loop until y is greater than x
        while(x>y){
            y+=i;
            i+=2;
            cnt++;
        }

    // return cnt as the square root of x
    return cnt;
    }
}

```

