Solution I:

- Time Complexity: O(1) as it uses a built-in function to calculate the square root.

Solution II:

- Time Complexity: O(x) as it iterates through all the numbers from 0 to x+1.

Solution III:

- Time Complexity: O(log n) as the binary search algorithm reduces the number of iterations by half on each iteration.

- Space complexity:
