I'm a visual learner so i have to map it out on piece of paper, to help me see it clearly, hope this can help you too.
Also I saw few people asking why `x / mid` instead of `mid * mid`, i was struggling to see it at first, but finally understood it. 
it's just a math trick.
```java
class Solution {
    public int mySqrt(int x) {
        int left = 1;
        int right = x;
        while (left <= right){
            // pervent overflow
            int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;
            // math concept of move multiplication to other side becomes division
            // (this)                       (here)      
            //  |                            |
            //  V                            V
            // mid * mid = x equals to  x / mid = mid
            // this also pervents overflow of mid * mid being too large
            if (mid > x / mid) right = mid - 1;
            else left = mid + 1;
        }

        return right;
    }
}
