# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Newton's method is taught in Calculus. Just use it to solve the problem
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The fomula for Newton's method for finding $\sqrt{a}$ is:
$$
x_{n+1}=x_n-\frac{f(x_n)}{f'(x_n)}
$$
where $f(x)=x^2-a$, $f'(x)=2x$ is the first derivative. The sequence $\{ x_n\}$ converges to $\sqrt{a}$.
