# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

find the largest `n` that `n * n <= x`. The largest possible number is `x // 2 + 1`, and smallest is `0`. so use binary search to find `n`.

why `mid = low + (high - low + 1) // 2`?
Because we update high value with `high = mid - 1`, we need to set mid closer to `high`, or we will have infinite loop if:
`mid = low = high + 1`, so `mid = (low + high) //2` and `mid * mid <= x`.

why `left < right` rather than `left <= right`?
`left <= right` will also lead to infinite loop when:
`left = right = mid` and `mid * mid <= x`.


