##  Why Binary Search ?

    As we know realtion between x and x*x increase monotonically
	(i.e always increasing in nature) so the intution is as follows.

    The square root of number would lie between 0<= (Square Root)< x 
	(where x is number itself) so we can apply BS where start =0 and end =x
    calculate mid and if(mid*mid == x) then mid is ans and if(mid*mid < x)
	then it is sure that all number's square before mid would be smaller than x 
	, Hence we would search in right hand side of mid i.e start = mid+1.
    Notice , But mid could be posible ans too ( For Example condider x = 8) so 
	store mid in ans variable

    In case when mid*mid > x then we would search in left hand side of mid by doing this 
	: end = mid-1;

